<section id="faq">
  <div
    class="mx-auto w-full lg:px-24 max-w-7xl md:px-12 items-center px-8 py-24 scroll-mt-12"
  >
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6 lg:gap-12">
      <div class="text-center lg:text-left">
        <div>
          <p
            class="text-3xl font-normal tracking-tight text-black font-display"
          >
            Frequently asked questions
          </p>
          <p class="text-base mt-4 text-zinc-500">
            Answers to commonly asked questions about our platform
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div
        x-data="{
  activeAccordion: '',
  setActiveAccordion(id) {
  this.activeAccordion = (this.activeAccordion == id) ? '' : id
  }
  }"
        class="relative w-full mx-auto font-normal lg:col-span-2"
      >
        <div
          x-data="{ id: $id('accordion') }"
          :class="{ 'text-black': activeAccordion==id, 'text-zinc-600 hover:text-accent-500': activeAccordion!=id }"
          class="cursor-pointer group text-black"
        >
          <button
            @click="setActiveAccordion(id)"
            class="flex items-center justify-between w-full p-4 pb-1 text-left font-medium select-none"
          >
            <span>What is Chaski?</span>
            <svg
              class="w-5 h-5 duration-300 ease-out text-accent-500 -rotate-[45deg]"
              :class="{ '-rotate-[45deg]': activeAccordion==id }"
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke-width="1.5"
              stroke="currentColor"
              ><path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                d="M12 6v12m6-6H6"></path></svg
            >
          </button>
          <div x-show="activeAccordion==id" x-collapse="">
            <div class="p-4 pt-2 text-zinc-500">
              Chaski is a privacy-focused, minimalist feed reader that allows you to consume content without ads, algorithms, or tracking. It lets you choose what you read, how you read it, and when—on your own terms.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div
          x-data="{ id: $id('accordion') }"
          :class="{ 'text-black': activeAccordion==id, 'text-zinc-600 hover:text-accent-500': activeAccordion!=id }"
          class="cursor-pointer group text-zinc-600 hover:text-accent-500"
        >
          <button
            @click="setActiveAccordion(id)"
            class="flex items-center justify-between w-full p-4 pb-1 text-left font-medium select-none"
          >
            <span
              >How does Chaski respect my privacy?</span
            >
            <svg
              class="w-5 h-5 duration-300 ease-out text-accent-500"
              :class="{ '-rotate-[45deg]': activeAccordion==id }"
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke-width="1.5"
              stroke="currentColor"
              ><path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                d="M12 6v12m6-6H6"></path></svg
            >
          </button>
          <div
            x-show="activeAccordion==id"
            x-collapse=""
            style="display: none;"
          >
            <div class="p-4 pt-2 text-zinc-500">
              Chaski does not collect any personal data, track your activity, or serve ads. Everything happens locally on your device, so you can enjoy reading without interruptions or privacy concerns.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div
          x-data="{ id: $id('accordion') }"
          :class="{ 'text-black': activeAccordion==id, 'text-zinc-600 hover:text-accent-500': activeAccordion!=id }"
          class="cursor-pointer group text-zinc-600 hover:text-accent-500"
        >
          <button
            @click="setActiveAccordion(id)"
            class="flex items-center justify-between w-full p-4 pb-1 text-left font-medium select-none"
          >
          <span>
            Can I sync my feeds across multiple devices? 
          </span>
            <svg
              class="w-5 h-5 duration-300 ease-out text-accent-500"
              :class="{ '-rotate-[45deg]': activeAccordion==id }"
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke-width="1.5"
              stroke="currentColor"
              ><path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                d="M12 6v12m6-6H6"></path></svg
            >
          </button>
          <div
            x-show="activeAccordion==id"
            x-collapse=""
            style="display: none;"
          >
            <div class="p-4 pt-2 text-zinc-500">
              Currently, Chaski does not support native sync across devices. However, this is a feature we plan to introduce soon, first through third-party services like Feeder, and eventually with native support.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div
          x-data="{ id: $id('accordion') }"
          :class="{ 'text-black': activeAccordion==id, 'text-zinc-600 hover:text-accent-500': activeAccordion!=id }"
          class="cursor-pointer group text-zinc-600 hover:text-accent-500"
        >
          <button
            @click="setActiveAccordion(id)"
            class="flex items-center justify-between w-full p-4 pb-1 text-left font-medium select-none"
          >
            <span>
              Can I migrate my feeds from another RSS reader to Chaski?
            </span
            >
            <svg
              class="w-5 h-5 duration-300 ease-out text-accent-500"
              :class="{ '-rotate-[45deg]': activeAccordion==id }"
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke-width="1.5"
              stroke="currentColor"
              ><path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                d="M12 6v12m6-6H6"></path></svg
            >
          </button>
          <div
            x-show="activeAccordion==id"
            x-collapse=""
            style="display: none;"
          >
            <div class="p-4 pt-2 text-zinc-500">
              Yes! Chaski supports importing and exporting OPML files, which is compatible with most major feed readers. Simply export your feeds from your current service and import them into Chaski.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div
          x-data="{ id: $id('accordion') }"
          :class="{ 'text-black': activeAccordion==id, 'text-zinc-600 hover:text-accent-500': activeAccordion!=id }"
          class="cursor-pointer group text-zinc-600 hover:text-accent-500"
        >
          <button
            @click="setActiveAccordion(id)"
            class="flex items-center justify-between w-full p-4 pb-1 text-left font-medium select-none"
          >
            <span>
              Does Chaski have an app for mobile devices? 
            </span>
            <svg
              class="w-5 h-5 duration-300 ease-out text-accent-500"
              :class="{ '-rotate-[45deg]': activeAccordion==id }"
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke-width="1.5"
              stroke="currentColor"
              ><path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                d="M12 6v12m6-6H6"></path></svg
            >
          </button>
          <div
            x-show="activeAccordion==id"
            x-collapse=""
            style="display: none;"
          >
            <div class="p-4 pt-2 text-zinc-500">
              At the moment, Chaski is available for Windows, macOS, and Linux. We do not have a mobile app yet, but it is something we're considering for the future. Stay tuned!
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div
          x-data="{ id: $id('accordion') }"
          :class="{ 'text-black': activeAccordion==id, 'text-zinc-600 hover:text-accent-500': activeAccordion!=id }"
          class="cursor-pointer group text-zinc-600 hover:text-accent-500"
        >
          <button
            @click="setActiveAccordion(id)"
            class="flex items-center justify-between w-full p-4 pb-1 text-left font-medium select-none"
          >
            <span>How is Chaski funded?</span>
            <svg
              class="w-5 h-5 duration-300 ease-out text-accent-500"
              :class="{ '-rotate-[45deg]': activeAccordion==id }"
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke-width="1.5"
              stroke="currentColor"
              ><path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                d="M12 6v12m6-6H6"></path></svg
            >
          </button>
          <div
            x-show="activeAccordion==id"
            x-collapse=""
            style="display: none;"
          >
            <div class="p-4 pt-2 text-zinc-500">
              Chaski is a personal side project I created to learn Rust. It's open-source and free to use. If you enjoy the app and want to support its development, you can buy me a coffee! Feedback and contributions are also always welcome.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div
          x-data="{ id: $id('accordion') }"
          :class="{ 'text-black': activeAccordion==id, 'text-zinc-600 hover:text-accent-500': activeAccordion!=id }"
          class="cursor-pointer group text-zinc-600 hover:text-accent-500"
        >
          <button
            @click="setActiveAccordion(id)"
            class="flex items-center justify-between w-full p-4 pb-1 text-left font-medium select-none"
          >
            <span
              >I can't install Chaski on macOS, what should I do?</span
            >
            <svg
              class="w-5 h-5 duration-300 ease-out text-accent-500"
              :class="{ '-rotate-[45deg]': activeAccordion==id }"
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke-width="1.5"
              stroke="currentColor"
              ><path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                d="M12 6v12m6-6H6"></path></svg
            >
          </button>
          <div
            x-show="activeAccordion==id"
            x-collapse=""
            style="display: none;"
          >
            <div class="p-4 pt-2 text-zinc-500">
              Currently, Chaski isn't fully tested or signed for macOS, as I don't have the required hardware for testing. If you can try the app on macOS and provide feedback, it would be much appreciated! Please note that you may encounter security warnings since the app is not signed.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div
          x-data="{ id: $id('accordion') }"
          :class="{ 'text-black': activeAccordion==id, 'text-zinc-600 hover:text-accent-500': activeAccordion!=id }"
          class="cursor-pointer group text-zinc-600 hover:text-accent-500"
        >
          <button
            @click="setActiveAccordion(id)"
            class="flex items-center justify-between w-full p-4 pb-1 text-left font-medium select-none"
          >
            <span>I get a warning when installing on Windows, what is it?</span>
            <svg
              class="w-5 h-5 duration-300 ease-out text-accent-500"
              :class="{ '-rotate-[45deg]': activeAccordion==id }"
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke-width="1.5"
              stroke="currentColor"
              ><path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                d="M12 6v12m6-6H6"></path></svg
            >
          </button>
          <div
            x-show="activeAccordion==id"
            x-collapse=""
            style="display: none;"
          >
            <div class="p-4 pt-2 text-zinc-500">
              On Windows, you might see a warning because Chaski is not digitally signed. This happens because it’s an open-source project and not distributed through official channels like the Microsoft Store. You can still install it, just be sure to download it from the GitHub releases.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
